HEADWORD: Stromeyerite
<hw>Stro"mey`er*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named from
the German chemist Friedrich <ets>Stromeyer</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A steel-gray mineral of metallic luster. It is a
sulphide of silver and copper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strond</ent>⟦br⟧
